cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for estimating the global scale of a 3D reconstructed model within a monocular SLAM algorithm using object detection.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the proposed method can be applied to robotics applications such as autonomous navigation.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the proposed method uses a Bayesian framework to integrate height priors over detected objects based on recent advances in fast generic object detection.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a probabilistic approach for global scale estimation.
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper presents promising results of the proposed approach obtained on several experiments with different object classes.
